      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 9.92,
      "text": "This is a LibriBox recording. All LibriBox recordings are in the public domain. For more information, archival and tier, please visit LibriBox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 10.98,
      "end": 12.24,
      "text": "Recorded by Warrabs.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 14.44,
      "end": 17.92,
      "text": "Aesop Vails. The charcoal burner and the fule.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 19.12,
      "end": 22.6,
      "text": "There was once a charcoal burner who lived and worked by himself.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 23.64,
      "end": 27.68,
      "text": "A fule, however, happened to come and settle in the same neighborhood.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 28.74,
      "end": 34.86,
      "text": "And the charcoal burner, having made his acquaintance and finding he was an agreeable sort of fellow,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 35.54,
      "end": 37.9,
      "text": "ask him if he would come and share his house.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 39.48,
      "end": 41.92,
      "text": "We shall get to know one another better away.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 43.04,
      "end": 48.02,
      "text": "He said, and beside, our household expenses will be diminished.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 49.66,
      "end": 51.88,
      "text": "The fule thanked him, but replied.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 51.88,
      "end": 60.88,
      "text": "I couldn't think of it, sir. Why, everything I take such pains to whiten would be blackened in no time by your charcoal.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 63.26,
      "end": 65.76,
      "text": "And of the charcoal burner and the fule.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
